  "texts": [
    "Among these, TREPAN.",
    "Craven and Shavlik [17] stands out as one of the earliest explainers we examined.",
    "This algorithm induces a decision tree that approximates the outcome of a classifier.",
    "SAGE [18] uses shapley values to quantify the predictive power of individual input features at a global level while considering feature interactions.",
    "TREPAN constructs its tree using a hillclimbing search process and a gain ratio criterion to identify the best M-of-N splits for each node."
  ],
